                <p>All surveys covering a time span of ten years or more are labelled in the figure. Two thirds of these long-running surveys cover either Europe and Central Asia or North America. The two longest-running surveys are the Panel Study of Income Dynamics (2) and the American Housing Survey (7), both of which are national surveys in the United States.</p>
            </sec>
